text: Duplicaria dussumieri, common name Dussumier's auger, is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Terebridae, the auger snails. ==Description== The length of the shell varies between 40 mm and 112 mm. ==Distribution== This marine species occurs off Indonesia, China, Japan and Korea ==References== ==External links== * Category:Terebridae Category:Gastropods described in 1839
title: Duplicaria dussumierii
